
'''The Compassionate Instinct: The [[Science of Human Goodness]], coedited by Dacher Keltner, Jason Marsh, and Jeremy Adam Smith (January, WW Norton), 2009'''


=Description=

""In these pages you will hear from Steven Pinker, who asks, 'Why is there peace?'; Robert Sapolsky, who examines violence among primates; Paul Ekman, who talks with the Dalai Lama about global compassion; Daniel Goleman, who proposes 'constructive anger'; and many others... A collection of personal stories and empirical research, The Compassionate Instinct will make you think not only about what it means to be happy and fulfilled but also about what it means to lead an ethical and compassionate life."
(http://shareable.net/blog/six-books-in-2010)


